\par \pard\plain \s18\widctlpar \f11\fs20 {\f4 Several interesting challenges await you on this level. Here are some tips on dealing with them:
\par 
\par }\pard \s18\fi-426\li426\widctlpar {\f4 1.\tab Starting out...
\par }\pard \s18\li426\widctlpar {\f4 Pause the ga
me to look around. You start out with a city that will soon burn to the ground if you do nothing about it. Some houses are already on fire. Delete the buildings next to them, to give yourself a fire barrier (so the fire can't spread).
\par 
\par Turn on the fire risk overlay, and delete the houses that are going to catch fire at any moment. If you don't want to get rid of the houses entirely, undo the deletes. This kicks the residents out, but leaves the house intact. The fire risk is neutralised
 until someone else moves into the house.
\par 
\par Now look around the road network, and build half a dozen or so prefects at strategic locations. Tell your labor advisor to set prefects as the no. 2 priority. Religion should always be no. 1 of course.
\par 
\par Build a temple to Mars, and two to Neptune.
\par 
\par Delete all facilities that are not needed, such as entertainment and education, markets, granary, fruit farms, and forum.
\par 
\par There's a group of zebras in the southeast edge. This is where you will be attacked from VERY SHORTLY. You have insuffi
cient time to build up soldiers or towers right there to repel them, so just build some walls to slow them down (at least 4 to 5 layers thick), and give your barracks enough time to train some tower guards for your city walls. These barbarians will make a
 beeline for your city. Note the direction of their attack, and bulk up the walls in that direction with towers. Remove towers from other parts, but fill the left over gaps with walls.
\par }\pard \s18\widctlpar {\f4 
\par }\pard \s18\fi-426\li426\widctlpar {\f4 2.\tab After the towers take care of the barbarians, spend the next few yea
rs building your city away from the starting position, but build slowly. Your export earnings on this level are far below Tarsus and Valentia, so exercise some patience.
\par 
\par 3.\tab Reserve the space between the coast and the central farmland, for your palace block. Build your plebian houses around the other couple of oasis.
\par 
\par 4.\tab When the invasions come, you will have a real fight on your hands. Towers alone are no longer sufficient to defeat the invaders. Prepare your troops for battle.
\par 
\par 5.\tab When Caesar requests an army, send at least 4 of your 6 legions, and you will win a Triumphal Arch.
